The array of square rock tiles wraps around the perimeter of the fountain. Many of them are weathered, uneven, and cracked
The tiles are much too heavy to lift with your hands.
You pry one of the tiles up, but all revealed is only a square dirt indentation in the ground. Tired, you drop the tile back into the hole to avoid tripping.
